    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (80.98) headlining the outfield as our premier start. His elevated score is driven by a favorable matchup against Kelly, where the combination of the pitcher\u2019s slow delivery and a wind-out environment creates an elite environment for his stolen base potential, which remains our primary focus. **Junior Caminero** (73.06) also presents a high-ceiling option in the utility slot; despite a slight park penalty, his matchup against Mahle is bolstered significantly by his projected efficiency against a pitcher with an xERA of 4.60. Meanwhile, **Trea Turner** (69.28) remains a foundational play at shortstop, with his leadoff role and the high-volume stolen base opportunity against Paddack anchoring his strong projection.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Jerar Encarnacion**, whose score of 42.40 landed just outside our starting rotation. While his platoon advantage against Matz was enticing, the optimizer favored the higher cumulative efficiency of our outfield depth, specifically the situational upside of **Hyeseong Kim** and **Carson Benge**. We are carefully monitoring **Yordan Alvarez** (60.46), as he faces a tough left-on-left dynamic against Suarez; while his xwOBA of 0.430 is elite, the platoon penalty keeps his score in the mid-tier. We continue to hold **Christian Yelich** on the IL and will look to re-integrate players like **Lars Nootbaar** or **Zac Veen** should our current lineup experience any late-scratch volatility. Managers should keep a close eye on the weather report, specifically the wind patterns that are providing a small, but necessary, boost to **Pete Crow-Armstrong** and **Hyeseong Kim**.",
